         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Should I cite your son's first name ¶  with the plants he discovered at the Adelaide River as an encouragement to him? ¶  What is his baptismal name? ¶ 1108  ¶ Selaginella holtzei ¶  F. Muell. ¶  ¶...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">90.10.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Maurice Holtze</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">GRG 19/391, State Records of South Australia, Adelaide.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Undated fragment. The letter must be later than the initial listing of number 1108 in the initial listing of specimens reported as arrived in M. to M. Holtze, 2 October 1890.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #c00000; ">Currently 90-10-00a, and probably others to be merged with it. Until that is dated can do no more on this. </seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sollte ich zur Ermuthigung Ihres Sohnes Vornamen bei den Pfl.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Pflanzen.</p>
               </note> angeben die er am Adelaide Fluss entdeckte? Was ist sein Tauf-Name?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">1108 Selaginella Holtzei, F.V.M. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ist wohl stets einjährig?</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Should I cite your son's first name<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M evidently did not receive the son's name in time to include it in the MS of the description of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Utricularia capilliflora</seg>, read at the 5 November 1890 meeting of the Royal Society of New South Wales and published as the final part of <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B91.05.07, p. 176, where the collector is described as 'Mr Holtze junior'. Letters concerning <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Utriculara</seg> indicate that the son was Nicholas, as does B93.03.05, p. 175, where the collection details for <seg style="font-style: italic; ">U. kamienskii</seg> are 'Near the Adelaide-River; M. and N. Holtze'. M knew the son's name was Nicholas after he received his essay, 'An acrid secretion from the seeds of a species of Grevillea', which was enclosed with M. Holtze to M, 9 January 1891.<seg style="color: #c00000; font-weight: bold; "> </seg>
                  </p>
               </note> with the plants he discovered at the Adelaide River as an encouragement to him?<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Specimen numbers within the range of the collection reported as arrived in M to M. Holtze include the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Utricularia</seg> specimens, attributed as joint collections in MEL</p>
               </note> What is his baptismal name?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">1108 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Selaginella%20holtzei">Selaginella holtzei</name>
               </seg> F. Muell.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">No publication of this name has been found (APNI, accessed 6 August 2022)</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #c00000; font-weight: bold; ">It would help if the label on MEL 2143604 </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #c00000; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; ">Selaginella uliginosa </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #c00000; font-weight: bold; ">could be checked which would enable us to see whether M had recognised that it was a previously described species—i.e., has it an initial S. holtzei label, deleted?</seg>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; "> </seg>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; background-color: #ffff00; ">No. Labelled 1890 Port Darwin</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I suppose it is always annual?</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Selaginella%20holtzei">Selaginella holtzei</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
